title: 'PITFALL: Similarly, the * can be omitted from value receivers created from pointers.'
pid: 7a7b77f9-05dc-46d9-8643-d4fd8726257c
body: |2-
  That is, if the following type signatures apply:
    func f (Vertex)
    func (Vertex) m
    var v Vertex
  then
    f(&v)    // does not work
    f(v)     // works
    (&v).m() // works, due to shorthand
    v.m()    // works
